President Muhammadu Buhari has in line with their enabling laws reconstituted the Governing Councils of the 25 Federal Polytechnics and 21 Colleges of Education, in the country. In a statement, Sonny Echono, the Permanent Secretary, Federal Ministry of Education, Abuja said that for the Federal Polytechnic, Ukana, Akwa Ibom State, the President appointed a five-member Governing Council, chaired by Chief Yemi Sanusi. The statement said Yahaya Garba (Niger), Bashir Kazaure (Jigawa), Tunde Oladunoye (Ogun) and Chris Azebamwan,  Edo State Publicity Secretary of the ruling APC were also appointed as members of the Governing council. For the governing council of the Hussaini Adamu Federal Polytechnic, Kazaure, Jigawa State, the President also named Ali Hussaini as chairman. It said that other members of the Governing council are Dr Timothy Ornguga (Benue),  Sani Mafara (member) and Alhaji Isa Jibrin (Niger) and Chief Francis Omoh, Edo State Welfare Secretary of the APC. Echono said that all the councils will be inaugurated by the Education Minister Mallam Adamu Adamu on April 20  at the National Universities Commission Auditorium, Abuja.